          </p>

          <div class="bg-gray-900/50 backdrop-blur-sm border-l-[3px] border-blue-400 pl-6 py-4 rounded-r">
            <p class="text-gray-200"><strong class="text-white">Quick answer:</strong> <span class="text-blue-300 font-black">10Web (9.3/10)</span> for WordPress education features (calendars, faculty, LMS). <span class="text-blue-300 font-black">Webflow (8.6/10)</span> for modern educational design that builds credibility.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm text-gray-400">
            <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-400 rounded-full"></span>
              40+ hours testing school websites
            </span>
            <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-400 rounded-full"></span>
              5 platforms analyzed
            </span>
            <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-blue-400 rounded-full"></span>
              Real school case study
            </span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- MY EXPERIENCE: THE SCHOOL WITH EMPTY SEATS -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-5xl">
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 border-[3px] border-blue-400 p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">My Experience: Why Parents Choose Waitlists Over Open Seats</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 uppercase tracking-wider font-black mb-8">Westfield Academy, Seattle WA | 2023 Real Case Study</p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <div class="bg-blue-100 border-l-[3px] border-blue-700 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-blue-800 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE BEFORE (February 2023)</p>
            <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Westfield Academy, K-12 private school in Seattle WA (established 2011). $25,000 annual tuition. Strong academics: 94% college placement, 12:1 student-teacher ratio. Website from 2012: broken on mobile, curriculum buried 6 clicks deep, no virtual tour, faculty listed as names only. 47 open seats despite strong academics. Competitor 2 miles away (same tuition, similar stats): beautiful Webflow site with curriculum pages, principal video, faculty bios with photos, event calendar prominent. They had a 40-family waitlist. Westfield's director: "We're better educators, but they win the enrollment game."</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-blue-100 border-l-[3px] border-blue-700 pl-6 py-5 rounded-r">
            <p class="text-sm font-black text-blue-800 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">THE FIX (March 2023)</p>
