            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Where's the curriculum?" - 73% left without finding answer</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Private school buried curriculum 6 clicks deep. Analytics: 73% of parents left within 60 seconds, never found curriculum page. Moved curriculum to homepage, added PDF download: 47% longer visit duration, 3x inquiry rate. Parents care what kids will learn. Hide it, they assume worst. Curriculum is your product - feature it.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Faculty page with photos + bios: parents "felt connection" before open house</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">K-12 school had faculty names only. Added professional photos + 2-sentence bios + "Why I teach." Open house feedback: "I already felt like I knew Mr. Chen from your website." Parents entrust children to humans, not institutions. Show them the humans. Build emotional connection before they visit.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Can't find event calendar" - 47 parents called daily, web team wasted 4 hours/day</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">School had calendar, buried under "Parent Resources ‚Üí Current Families ‚Üí Important Links ‚Üí Calendar." 47 parents called daily asking events. Moved calendar to main navigation: calls dropped to 4/day. Web team saved 12 hours/week. Poor information architecture = real staff time cost. Make critical features impossible to miss.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">$8K tuition, 2005 website = 23% of parents assumed school underfunded</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Private school $8K/year, website looked ancient. Parent survey: 23% assumed school was underfunded due to dated website. "If they can't invest in their website, can they invest in my child's education?" Perception matches reality online. Modern website = perceived investment in educational quality.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-blue-600 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Alumni success stories on homepage = 67% increase in tour requests</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-2">Private school buried college placement data 5 clicks deep. Added alumni success stories prominently on homepage: 67% increase in tour requests. Parents want proof of outcomes. "Where will my child be after this school?" is the #1 parent question. Answer it immediately and visually.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- TOOL COMPARISONS -->
